 notes:</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/07/11/powerpress-version-7-1-including-apple-ios-11-support/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PowerPress Update</a><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.brandingbrews.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Branding Brews</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/sarahrheawerner/2017/06/15/how-aaron-mahnke-makes-a-living-podcasting-and-how-you-can-too/4/#5eb82e6c93f5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How Aaron Mahnke Makes A Living Podcasting (And How You Can Too)</a><br />\n<a href=\"http://I wish I had thought of this resource when we were talking about monetization and selling merchandise. https://www.printful.com/  Printful is awesome. You can connect it with a number of website platforms. Customer orders a product on your site, it gets sent to Printful, they print and ship it to your customer. You don\'t ever have to pre-order products so no inventory or big up-front costs!\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Printful</a> &#8211; After the recording Ryan thought of a useful company for merchandise. You can connect it with a number of website platforms. Customers order a product on your site, it gets sent to Printful, they print and ship it to your customer. You don&#8217;t even have to pre-order products so no inventory or big up-front costs!</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/07/17/podcasting-updates-advice-and-experiences/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"PowerPress Version 7.1 Including Apple iOS 11 Support Is Here! - PowerPress Podcast\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/07/11/powerpress-version-7-1-including-apple-ios-11-support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:103:\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/07/11/powerpress-version-7-1-including-apple-ios-11-support/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 11 Jul 2017 20:08:18 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Blubrry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/?p=5817\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:635:\"PowerPress, the number one podcasting plugin with over 1 million downloads worldwide, has just launched PowerPress version 7.1. Here&#8217;s what you can expect from the new version. New Tagging: As you may already know, in iOS version 11, Apple added new tags to provide better support for serialized content, and these are now supported in &#8230; <a href=\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/07/11/powerpress-version-7-1-including-apple-ios-11-support/\" class=\"more-link\">Continue reading <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">PowerPress Version 7.1 Including Apple iOS 11 Support Is Here!</span> <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Blubrry\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3902:\"<p><a href=\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/pplugin1.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-5806\" src=\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/pplugin1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"137\" height=\"98\" /></a>PowerPress, the number one podcasting plugin with over <a href=\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/03/22/powerpress-tops-1-million-downloads/\">1 million downloads worldwide,</a> has just launched <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/powerpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PowerPress version 7.1</a>. Here&#8217;s what you can expect from the new version.</p>\n<h3>New Tagging:</h3>\n<p>As you may already know, in iOS version 11, Apple added new tags to provide better support for serialized content, and these are now supported in PowerPress 7.1, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>iTunes:type,iTunes:episode, and iTunes:season:</strong>These tags were added to support serialized content. &#8220;Before this, all podcasts were assumed to be episodic,&#8221; explains Angelo Mandato, CIO of Blubrry.</li>\n<li><strong>iTunes:episodeType</strong>: &#8220;This tag adds a way to mark special episodes,&#8221; says Mandato.</li>\n<li><strong>iTunes:title:</strong> &#8220;At the episode level, this is Apple&#8217;s solutionfor podcasters who add episode numbers and other extra information to their blog post titles. The iTunes title should be clean of such meta information, since this information can now be specified by the other new tags previously mentioned.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>content:encoded &amp;</strong><strong><strong>iTunes:summary: </strong></strong>This is a value containing the show notes for your episode. PowerPress has supported these tags for many years.<strong><strong><br />\n</strong></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&#8220;We&#8217;ve known the content:encoded tag was necessary for years,&#8221; explains Mandato. &#8220;We have worked with the Apple team confirming we are in full compliance of Apple&#8217;s latest documentation.&#8221; Check out this helpful PDF from Apple laying out the new and updated specs to <a href=\"http://podcasts.apple.com/resources/spec/ApplePodcastsSpecUpdatesiOS11.pdf\">learn more about Apple Podcasts and tagging in iOS 11</a>.</p>\n<h3>Other Additions:</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://create.blubrry.com/resources/powerpress/powerpress-beta/\">Powerpress Version 7.1</a> contains a few other upgrades and improvements, such as:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Subscribe on iTunes</em> has been changed to <em>Subscribe on Apple Podcasts</em>.</li>\n<li>Secure HTTPS websites using Blubrry Podcast Media Hosting are now automatically supported. Media URLs are now automatically converted to HTTPS. You no longer have to edit past episodes if you switch from HTTP to HTTPS.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please see the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/powerpress/#developers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">change log</a> for a full list of upgrades and improvements.</p>\n<h3>Something we hope you won&#8217;t miss:</h3>\n<p>A barely-used feature has been removed due to being outdated and seldom-used. The Windows Media Player embed for wmv video and wma audio has been removed. Chrome, Safari, Firefox as well as Microsoft Edge browsers do not support the Windows Media Player embed, providing support for this is no longer practical. In its place will be a play link which will open the media on the device&#8217;s default media player.</p>\n<h3>Some not-so-fine print:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>PowerPress 7.1 requires WordPress version 3.6 or newer. WordPress 4.8+ is recommended.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Ready to try <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/powerpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PowerPress 7.1</a>, the very latest version of the world&#8217;s most popular podcasting plugin? <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/powerpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Here&#8217;s where to get your FREE download</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/07/11/powerpress-version-7-1-including-apple-ios-11-support/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"PowerPress 7.1 With all the iOS 11 features  Your Podcast 009 - PowerPress Podcast\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://powerpresspodcast.com/2017/07/10/powerpress-7-1-your-podcast-009/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_