(405, 1, '2017-07-17 04:42:55', '2017-07-17 04:42:55', '<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 inner-content\">\r\n<p>NetworkRv was formed in June 2017 by Doug Curtis a former Executive with Dometic and Brian Gibson a Marketing Consultant of Monopolize Marketing. Doug and Brian have a combined 50 years of marketing experience with businesses of all sizes and from all industries.</p>\r\n<p>The company was formed to provide a needed service to both manufacturers of RV equipment and Dealers of RV Equipment as a way to introduce new products into the marketplace and provide product reviews and product education to both the Dealers and to their customers, the end users.</p>\r\n<p><h4>The Editor - Doug Curtis:</h4>\r\nSeeking to write a great American novel, my life became a terrific adventure story. Imagine journeying by bus, Land Rover, train, sailboat, powerboat, and single-engine plane from Guadalajara to Machu Picchu to Nairobi to Kealakekua. Backpacking, tent camping, and van camping through 67 US state and national parks, and scaring myself by canoeing in an early October blizzard in the Grand Tetons. Kayaking 86 miles through the Sea of Cortez with the National Outdoor Leadership School (NOLS), and naively cross-country skiing into a herd of wild Buffalo in Wyoming. Then realizing, after all those experiences, that burning the candle at both ends and having bizarre conversations with many peculiar storytellers at more than 1,000 campfires failed to produce the next great American novel!</p>\r\n<p>Like many dreamy adventurers, I planned to sail from Hawaii to Polynesia, but I havent made it yet. Instead, I moved from Hawaii to Ft. Lauderdale to sail a 46 Nova Scotia schooner to St. Barts. I survived a few scary storms at sea, but Im thankful for encountering mostly sunny skies and smooth sailing. After owning a few boats, I realized I needed a better boat, so I had to go back to work to earn a bucket of money. That path led to my wonderful wife and two daughters, so it was clearly the right decision.</p>\r\n<p>As my career journey progressed, I worked as a filmmaker, TV producer and direct-response marketer. I stretched my brain at advertising agencies, business start-ups and corporate consulting. One of my consulting clients was Dometic, an international consumer-products manufacturer based in Sweden. Recruited by the Dometic Americas president, I enjoyed aligning the sales and marketing strategies for the RV, Marine, Truck & Automotive sales teams. Achieving 17 industry awards for new product-launch strategies and launching over 115 products to engage the OEM & Aftermarket buyers, my focus sharpened.</p>\r\n<p>After ten years of working with the largest global marine and RV accessory manufacturer, I saw a strong opportunity to help smaller companies quicken growth using strategies that worked so well for me with the Dometic brands. Of course, what works for big brands doesnt always work for smaller companiesbut the principles of marketing are exactly the same.</p>\r\n<p>Working hands-on with companies in the $1 million to $100 million revenue range allowed me to see how valuable those principles can be, when tailored to a smaller companys needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I developed a process to help brands quickly find the right messageand the right marketing mixto spend more efficiently and outperform competitors. I\'m delighted that the internet has become the new TV, and Im invigorating my lifework and adventuring experience to deliver great products to the mobile-living community, whether they are on a boat, or RV.</p>\r\n<p>As an experienced executive marketing leader, I move marketing from being considered a cost center to being a strategic source of revenue. I develop and manage a multi-industry, multi-national digital information organization to drive and support international sales.</p>\r\n<p>Businesses and people who love adventure continuously encounter challenges and search for answers to their problems. My current focus addresses these issues and provides solutions.</p>\r\n<p>In the coming year, one of my next outdoor adventures will be extreme ocean kayak sailing. In the meantime, I enjoy making new professional relationships, so contact me if you want to connect.</p>\r\n<h3>The founders\' resumes:</h3>\r\n<img src=\"http://webdeveloperlive.com/networkrv/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/doug.jpg\" class=\"contact-pic\" width=\"240\" height=\"340\" />\r\n<h4>Doug Curtis -Sales and Marketing Strategist</h4>\r\n<p>Doug Curtis leads the team to deliver its marketing strategy that includes strengthening the clients brand and helping to define its mission, vision, and purpose in the marketplace in both the United States, Europe, and Asia.Over the past 10 years, his brand positioning, strategy, and content marketing expertise leveraged the Demotic brands to become the $1.5 billion global manufacturing leader for accessory products for Marine, RV, Automotive, and Truck industries.</p>\r\n<p>Doug reported to the Americas president and lead 4 divisions and brands through periods of accelerated growth by driving promotional marketing and sales traffic of consumer product goods to the business market of OEMs, dealers, and retailers.\r\nResponsible for innovative planning, timeline management, scheduling, team formation, communications planning, and re-branding. Direction and responsible for all go-to-market activity in North and South American marketing; results-tracking and analysis; revenue reports to determine product trends and effectiveness in multiple markets.</p>\r\n<p>Recruited, trained, mentored, and developed marketing and sales staff throughout territory. Managed and evaluated effectiveness of existing and new sales and marketing channels, both direct and B2B. Ensured messaging and content adoption across multiple marketing channels and programs (digital campaigns, trade shows, events, digitalsales, channel partners, web, social media, etc.) Goal driven, results oriented sales and marketing executive with twenty years experience possessing strategic planning management, and P&L responsibility. Proven ability to implement organizational initiatives that consistently increase profitability and launch new products in global competitive international markets.</p>\r\n<h4>KEY ACHIEVEMENTS</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Spearheaded marketing and generation of $600M+ in annual B2B2C consumer product sales revenues</li>\r\n<li>Developed digital sales tools to maximize sales revenue increases of 7-10% each year for last 3 years</li>\r\n<li>Launched over 80 new products achieving 17 industry Innovation & Best Product awards</li>\r\n<li>Designed automotive marketing that achieved multi-million-dollar contract with GM in 23 months</li>\r\n<li>Introduced digital technological solutions resulting in $625,000 reduction in print costs over 5 years</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>PROFESSIONAL STRENGTHS</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strategic Planning & Growth</li>\r\n<li>New Account Growth & Development</li>\r\n<li>Start-up & Turnaround</li>\r\n<li>Key Account Management</li>\r\n<li>Contract Negotiation</li>\r\n<li>New Product Launch</li>\r\n<li>Systems Trend/Market Analysis</li>\r\n<li>Brand Recognition</li>\r\n<li>P & L Management</li>\r\n<li>Proactive Management</li>\r\n<li>Technology Project Management</li>\r\n<li>Digital Media Relations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>TV / VIDEO DIRECT RESPONSE ACCOMPLISHMENTS</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Launched financial services TV infomercial direct response 811 half-hour shows on Fox, PBS, Comcast </li>\r\n  <li>Achieved an additional $300 million in assets, accelerated income by 74% in five years </li>\r\n  <li>Electronic broadcast media - produced 4,000 TV commercials, 300+ corporate training videos </li>\r\n  <li>Doug Curtis has a Master&#8217;s degree from Alliant International University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Brian Gibson</h3>\r\n<img src=\"http://webdeveloperlive.com/networkrv/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/brian.jpg\" class=\"contact-pic\" width=\"240\" height=\"